        },
        "subject": "LU-64 Fix test conditions in stripe attr helpers",
        "message": "LU-64 Fix test conditions in stripe attr helpers\n\nIf $ACTUAL happened to be the empty string, the test to determine if an\nerror occurred would report a false pass. This patch fixes this\nissue by prepending the character 'x' to the variables during the\ncomparison.\n\nAlso, when an error is reported, the variables are now wrapped in single\nquotes. This makes the output more readable if one of the variables is\nthe empty string.\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Idd6564c2a0e6880dd3cd84d2385316380280cab2\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
